16/08/2005
MOSTAR, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Federation of BiH (FBiH) police said Monday (15 August) that a large amount of illegal weaponry and military equipment was found during a two-day police operation in the Mostar area of southern BiH. According to the announcement, an anonymous tip led local police to an area on the road connecting the villages of Goranica and Bogodola, where they discovered 50 containers of munitions. It was the largest stash seized in FBiH in the past five years, according to local prosecutors. (Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 16/08/05; PBS BiH, OHR Sources, NTV Hayat - 15/08/05) 
